            <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--on-surface-variant);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                In academic institutions, assigning supervisors to final-year projects is often manual and prone to unconscious bias. Students might be selected based on past grades, familiarity, or demographics rather than the strength of their innovative ideas.
